        "id": "c4eeadb4-e93d-4dfb-bf6a-1c6e29c83607",
        "text": "Holacracy has been compared to [[sociocracy]], a system of governance developed in the second half of the twentieth century.[ The Open-Source Everything Manifesto] Sociocracy had a significant early influence during the incubation of Holacracy, though Holacracy has increasingly differentiated away from it since then.[http://www.adeeperdemocracy.org/holacracy-sociocracy/ Holacracy and Sociocracy] Sociocracy particularly inspired the development of the circle structure and governance processes (described in more detail later) within Holacracy. Holacracy is designed for organizations and fundamentally differentiates the roles of the organization from the people working in it.[http://holacracy.org/resources/sociocracy-holacracy Sociocracy & Holacracy] - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Holacracy#Influences_and_comparable_systems wikipedia]"
