    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "e3a8e06961ab48f2",
      "text": "The term holacracy is derived from the term [[holarchy]], coined by [[Arthur Koestler]] in his 1967 book ''[[The Ghost in the Machine]]''. A holarchy is composed of holons ([[Holon (philosophy)]]) (Greek: ὅλον, holon neuter form of ὅλος, holos \"whole\") or units that are autonomous and self-reliant, but also dependent on the greater whole of which they are part. Thus a holarchy is a hierarchy of self-regulating holons that function both as autonomous wholes and as dependent parts."
    },
